Step-by-step how-tos for **infrequent** operational tasks — the things done
rarely enough that nobody remembers the steps. Each guide is self-contained and
written so a future session can repeat the task without re-deriving it.

> For the standing *engineering* rules (the confirmation ritual, verification
> discipline, etc.) see [`../PROJECT_RULES.md`](../PROJECT_RULES.md). For the
> **resume runbook** see [`../NEXT-STEPS.md`](../NEXT-STEPS.md). This folder is
> specifically for "how do I set up X again".

## What belongs here

- One-time or rare setup (provider/service registration, credential provisioning).
- Environment bring-up / onboarding a new environment.
- Operational runbooks (symptom → cause → fix, rotation calendars).
- Anything you'd otherwise re-derive painfully each time.

Routine, frequent commands belong in the repo [`../../README.md`](../../README.md),
not here.

